<li id="cite_note-36"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36" title="">^</a></b> as <a href="/wiki/Chaucer" title="Chaucer" class="mw-redirect">Chaucer</a> wrote in the <a href="http://ebooks.adelaide.edu.au/c/chaucer/canterbury/daniel/chapter13.html" class="external text" title="http://ebooks.adelaide.edu.au/c/chaucer/canterbury/daniel/chapter13.html" rel="nofollow">Monk's Tale</a>, "Redeth the grete poete of Ytaille / That highte Dant, for he kan al devyse / Fro point to point; nat o word wol he faille".</li>
